pdnPppMlMIB.name: pdnPppMlMIB
pdnPppMlMIB.organization: Paradyne Networks MIB Working Group Other information about group editing the MIB
pdnPppMlMIB.contactinfo: Paradyne Networks, Inc. 8545 126th Avenue North Largo, FL 33733 www.paradyne.com General Comments to: mibwg_team@paradyne.com Editor Clay Sikes
pdnPppMlMIB.description: The MIB module for configuring and managing multilink PPP. The following documents should be referenced with respect to this MIB: [PPP] Carlson, J, `PPP Design and Debugging', Addison-Wesley, December 1997. [RFC 1661] Simpson, W., `The Point-to-Point Protocol', July 1994. [RFC 1990] Sklower, K. et al., `The PPP Multilink Protocol (MP)', August 1996.

MRRU.name: MRRU
MRRU.description: Multilink Maximum Received Reconstructed Units (MMRU). The maximum number of octets in the Information Fields of reassembled packets.

SSNHF.name: SSNHF
SSNHF.description: The Short Sequence Number Header Format value.
SSNHF.reference: RFC 1990, Section 5.1.2, `Short Sequence Number Header Option'.

pdnPppMlBundleNumber.name: pdnPppMlBundleNumber
pdnPppMlBundleNumber.description: The number of multilink PPP bundles configured on this system.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigTable.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigTable
pdnPppMlBundleConfigTable.description: The Multilink PPP Bundle Configuration Table.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigEntry.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigEntry
pdnPppMlBundleConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Multilink PPP Configuration Table.

pdnPppMlBundleIfIndex.name: pdnPppMlBundleIfIndex
pdnPppMlBundleIfIndex.description: Identifies the interface number assigned to this bundle and is used to identify corresponding rows in the Interfaces MIB.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigRowStatus.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigRowStatus
pdnPppMlBundleConfigRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify, or delete rows in the table.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigMRRU.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigMRRU
pdnPppMlBundleConfigMRRU.description: The Multilink Maximum Received Reconstructed Units LCP option. This option specifies the maximum number of octets in the Information fields of reassembled packets.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigSSNHF.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigSSNHF
pdnPppMlBundleConfigSSNHF.reference: RFC 1990, Section 5.1.2, `Short Sequence Number Header Format Option'.
pdnPppMlBundleConfigSSNHF.description: The Short Sequence Number Header Format option. When set to enabled(1), the local PPP entity will indicate to the remote PPP entity that fragments with 12-bit sequence numbers are desired. When set to disabled(2), the local PPP entity will indicate to the remote PPP entity that fragments with 24-bit sequence numbers are desired.

pdnPppMlBundleConfigFragmentSize.name: pdnPppMlBundleConfigFragmentSize
pdnPppMlBundleConfigFragmentSize.reference: RFC 1990, Section 3, `Packet Formats'. `PPP Design and Debugging', page 121, `Fragmentation and Reassembly'.
pdnPppMlBundleConfigFragmentSize.description: Configures the maximum number of octets of data in the packet's fragment data field. The value `0' has a special meaning which is to say `fragmentation is disabled'.

pdnPppMlBundleMappingTable.name: pdnPppMlBundleMappingTable
pdnPppMlBundleMappingTable.description: The Multilink PPP Bundle Mapping Table. A table mapping the ifIndex of interfaces to a particular multilink PPP bundle identified by the pdnPppMlBundleIfIndex.

pdnPppMlBundleMappingEntry.name: pdnPppMlBundleMappingEntry
pdnPppMlBundleMappingEntry.description: Each row describes one ifIndex to pdnPppMlBundleIfIndex mapping.

pdnPppMlBundleMappingRowStatus.name: pdnPppMlBundleMappingRowStatus
pdnPppMlBundleMappingRowStatus.description: Used to create, modify, or delete rows in the table.

pdnPppMlBundleMappingBundleIfIndex.name: pdnPppMlBundleMappingBundleIfIndex
pdnPppMlBundleMappingBundleIfIndex.description: The pdnPppMlBundleIndex of the PPP bundle which implements the specified interface.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusTable.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusTable
pdnPppMlBundleStatusTable.description: The Multilink PPP Bundle Status Table.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusEntry.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusEntry
pdnPppMlBundleStatusEntry.description: An entry in the Multilink PPP Status Table.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusCurrState.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusCurrState
pdnPppMlBundleStatusCurrState.description: The current state of the ML PPP State Machine.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteMRRU.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteMRRU
pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteMRRU.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Multilink Maximum Received Reconstructed Units LCP option for the local to remote direction.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalMRRU.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalMRRU
pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalMRRU.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Multilink Maximum Received Reconstructed Units LCP option for the remote to local direction.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteSSNHF.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteSSNHF
pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteSSNHF.reference: RFC 1990, Section 5.1.2, `Short Sequence Number Header Format Option'.
pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteSSNHF.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Short Sequence Number Header Format option for the local to remote direction. If negotiation has not completed, ssnhfUnknown(1) will be returned.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalSSNHF.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalSSNHF
pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalSSNHF.reference: RFC 1990, Section 5.1.2, `Short Sequence Number Header Format Option'.
pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalSSNHF.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Short Sequence Number Header Format option for the remote to local direction. If negotiation has not completed, ssnhfUnknown(1) will be returned.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDClass.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDClass
pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDClass.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Endpoint Discriminator Option's class for the local PPP entity.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDAddr.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDAddr
pdnPppMlBundleStatusLocalToRemoteEDAddr.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Endpoint Discriminator Option's address for the local PPP entity.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDClass.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDClass
pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDClass.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Endpoint Discriminator Option's class for the remote PPP entity.

pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDAddr.name: pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDAddr
pdnPppMlBundleStatusRemoteToLocalEDAddr.description: Identifies the result of the negotiation for the Endpoint Discriminator Option's address for the remote PPP entity.

pdnPppMlCompliance.name: pdnPppMlCompliance
pdnPppMlCompliance.description: The compliance statement for network elements implementing multilink PPP.

pdnPppMlBundleDefinitionGroup.name: pdnPppMlBundleDefinitionGroup
pdnPppMlBundleDefinitionGroup.description: Define a bundle and map ifIndices to it.

pdnPppMlBundleStateMachineGroup.name: pdnPppMlBundleStateMachineGroup
pdnPppMlBundleStateMachineGroup.description: Displays the ML PPP State Machine's state.

pdnPppMlBundleMRRUGroup.name: pdnPppMlBundleMRRUGroup
pdnPppMlBundleMRRUGroup.description: Configures and displays the results of the negotiation of the Multilink Maximum Received Reconstructed Units LCP Option.

pdnPppMlBundleSSNHFGroup.name: pdnPppMlBundleSSNHFGroup
pdnPppMlBundleSSNHFGroup.description: Configures and displays the results of the negotiation of the Short Sequence Number Header Format Option.

pdnPppMlBundleEDGroup.name: pdnPppMlBundleEDGroup
pdnPppMlBundleEDGroup.description: Displays the results of the negotiation of the Endpoint Discriminator Option.
